Our thoughts are with Vivienne's family, friends and the Vivienne Westwood brand. 

We are proud to be working with the brand with our sun collections and optical launch with Specsavers. We hope to continue Vivienne’s spirit and legacy with the launch of SUN23 and future sun and optical collections.

On the 29th of December, Vivienne Westwood died peacefully at her home in Clapham, South London, surrounded by her friends and family at the age of 81.
 
A true icon of British high fashion, Vivienne Westwood began designing in 1971 in London. By the end of the 70s, she was considered a symbol of the British avant-garde having pioneered the punk look. This movement and the designs associated with anarchic and rebellious attitude influenced far beyond the fashion and music worlds and are still felt today. In 1989, Vivienne met Andreas Kronthaler, her future husband and long-time design partner and now Creative Director. Vivienne Westwood is one of the last independent global fashion brands and strives to be more than just a producer of clothes and accessories. The voice of the brand raises awareness of the environmental impact of overconsumption, urging people to buy less and buy better quality.
 
Vivienne’s innovation and ethos will be remembered and continue through design and activism. 

Our thoughts are with Vivienne's family, friends and the Vivienne Westwood brand. 

Our collaboration with such an iconic figure in the fashion industry is a privilege and brings so much creativity and inspiration to the optical industry.

We are proud to be working with the brand with our sun collections and optical launch with Specsavers. We hope to continue Vivienne’s spirit and legacy with the launch of SUN23 and future sun and optical collections.

Our thoughts are with Vivienne's family, friends and the Vivienne Westwood brand.

This International Women’s Day, we are celebrating our female-founded brands who have all made their mark on fashion.
 
In 1981 @karen_millen invested £100 in one thousand metres of white cotton and began crafting sleek white shirts for her friends. Today, Karen Millen is a well-established premium brand dedicated to high quality, flattering fit and scrupulous attention to design detail. Inspired by couture, Karen Millen’s mission is to create striking style-led pieces that resonate with women of all ages, united by their style attitude.
 
Our sun and optical collections are a confident expression of style and individuality, immaculately echoing the brand’s values of female empowerment and quality.
 
#InternationalWomensDay #KarenMillen #Mondottica

This International Women’s Day, we are celebrating our female-founded brands who have all made their mark on fashion.

In 1984, Evelyne Chetrite founded @sandroparis. Sandro is a leading accessible luxury Parisian brand with clean lines and sophisticated aesthetic showcased in its refined but versatile collections. Evelyne created a woman’s line that focused on modern and sophisticated styles, but with a hint of androgyny. In 2008, Evelyne’s son Ilan launched Sandro Homme which focused on bringing Sandro’s sensibility into a men’s collection by revisiting classics with modern twists in Sandro Homme.

In 1998, Evelyne’s sister Judith Milgrom founded @majeparis. Inspired by the reinvention of the Parisian woman, Judith’s goal to create a brand that would be cross-generational, celebrating women who like to dress is reflected in the brand‘s bold, modern and urban style. Over the years, Maje has successfully developed a wide collection ranging from ready-to-wear to accessories and has managed to establish itself as a leading brand of accessible luxury.

#InternationalWomensDay #Maje #Sandro #Mondottica

This International Women’s Day, we are celebrating our female-founded brands who have all made their mark on fashion.
 
A true icon of British high fashion, @viviennewestwood began designing in 1971 in London. By the end of the 70s, she was considered a symbol of the British avant-garde having pioneered the punk look. This movement and the designs associated with anarchic and rebellious attitude influenced far beyond the fashion and music worlds and are still felt today. In 1989, Vivienne met Andreas Kronthaler, her future husband and long-time design partner and now Creative Director.
 
Vivienne Westwood is one of the last independent global fashion brands and strives to be more than just a producer of clothes and accessories. The voice of the brand raises awareness of the environmental impact of overconsumption, urging people to buy less and buy better quality.
 
Vivienne’s innovation and ethos will be remembered and continue through design and activism.
 
In late 2022, Vivienne founded The Vivienne Foundation with her sons and granddaughter. The non-for-profit Foundation which launches next year will honour, protect and continue Vivienne’s legacy, her life, design and activism.
 
We hope to continue Vivienne’s spirit and legacy with our future sun and optical collections.

#InternationalWomensDay #VivienneWestwood #Mondottica

Good mental health is something at Mondottica, we aim to support at all times, but this week we are recognising Mental Health Awareness week by raising awareness around this year’s theme which is 'anxiety’.
 
This week, we are empowering our Mental Health first aiders to plan and lead 5 daily drop-in sessions to raise awareness of good mental health and remind our team of our year-round support.
 
#MentalHealthAwarenessWeek #Mondottica #MentalHealth

Supporting this year’s Mental Health awareness theme of anxiety, we’re opening up discussions to raise awareness of triggers, solutions and support so that all our Mondottica team can have the best mental health possible. Our MHFA team are running daily sessions to highlight the support available all year round.
 
#MentalHealthAwarenessWeek #Mondottica #MentalHealth

Supporting good mental health for all our employees is important every day. We’re proud of our Mental Health first aid team for running 5 daily drop in sessions this last week to raise awareness on anxiety, supporting this years Mental Health awareness week, and reminding our team of the importance of good mental health and the support available to achieve it 
 
#MentalHealthAwarenessWeek #Mondottica #MentalHealth

At Mondottica, two of our core values are respect and integrity. 

In celebration of Pride Month, our Diversity and Inclusion group hosted a ‘Lunch & Learn’ for our teams in Nottingham and London.
The aim of the session was to raise awareness and highlight the importance of Pride, its history and what we can do as individuals and as a business to support the LGBTQIA+ Community.

Our Diversity and Inclusion team meet every six weeks to discuss these important issues as well as other topics to further understand how we can improve and what actions we can take as a business, and to support and raise awareness to our employees. 

#PrideMonth #Pride #Diversity #Inclusion #Mondottica

Celebrating its 50th anniversary this year, @pepejeans has an enviable denim pedigree that has pioneered street style in the subsequent five decades. From the vibrant streets of Portobello, Pepe Jeans London is a denim pioneer that has consistently incorporated workwear aesthetics into contemporary streetwear to reflect the style of each new era. Associated with limitless creativity, Pepe Jeans London provides the building blocks of individuality, self-confidence, and authenticity.

This season’s eyewear collections for women and men offer an exciting mix of original designs with a youthful feel, embracing global street style and giving the wearer another way to express their individuality.

#PepeJeans #Mondottica #Eyewear #PepeJeans50

The @pepejeans AW23 optical collection, celebrates the roots of the London brand, the perfect accessory to mark the landmark 50th anniversary.

In bold Gloss Crystal Blue acetate, PJ3521 Juno for women is a pure 1980’s throwback. Its colourful design embodies Pepe Jeans London’s sense of individuality and swagger. The hand-filled enamel detailing on the temples and marbled acetate tips, taken from the capsule SUN23 Hero Project, provide stylish finishes.

The men’s model PJ3533 Nord in Gloss Grey Stripe strikes the perfect balance between work and play. The marbled grey acetate fascia contrasts perfectly with the electric blue temples. The Pepe Jeans London logo and stitching details are a nod to the brand’s denim heritage.

#PepeJeans #Mondottica #Eyewear #PepeJeans50

Emulating their adult counterparts, the @pepejeans Kid's optical collection celebrates the brand's individuality and denim heritage.

#PepeJeans #Mondottica #Eyewear #PepeJeans50

Today marks World Mental Health Day. Good mental health is something at Mondottica, we aim to always support. Today, we provided our employees with resources that they can access at all times, when they need support.

#WorldMentalHealthDay #Mondottica #MentalHealth #MentalHealthAwareness

As part of our recognition of World Mental Health Day, we empowered our employees to take an hour for ‘Tea & Talk’. 

Set up by Mental Health Foundation, a ‘Tea & Talk’ is a great way to get together with colleagues, friends and family members to raise money and awareness around Mental Health. 

#WorldMentalHealthDay #Mondottica #MentalHealth #MentalHealthAwareness

At Mondottica, we have Mental First Aiders, who had special training with Mental Health First Aid England and are equipped to identify the signs of mental ill-health issues, understand the range of issues and support our staff in a way that others might not know how. 

#WorldMentalHealthDay #Mondottica #MentalHealth #MentalHealthAwareness
